'''Harold "Howie" Weed''' (born [[December 23]], [[1960s#1962|1962]]) is an [[Industrial Light & Magic]] artist and occasional actor in the ''Star Wars'' saga. He played multiple background characters ([[Ketwol]], [[Melas]]) and the [[Wampa]] ice creature for the [[1997]] [[The Star Wars Trilogy Special Edition|Special Editions]].

==Biography==
In [[1997]], Harold Weed began working on the Special Editions of the ''Star Wars'' [[original trilogy]]. Weed was the chief creature maker for [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']] Special Editions, creating the new monsters for both these films.

Much like [[Rick Baker]] before him, Weed acted as some of his creations. Particularly, on [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']], he can be seen in the cantina as [[Ketwol]], as well as [[Melas]]. The same puppet was used for both characters. During ''The Empire Strikes Back'', Weed was chosen to be inside his own Wampa Ice Creature costume to film new scenes. Because this role no longer required a tall actor, [[Des Webb]] was not re-called. Thus, the "gory Wampa" in the Special Edition is mainly played by Weed.

Weed continued working for the ''Star Wars'' saga with [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']], working as a construction artist and digital model development artist for ILM.

